gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Rockets 123, Trail Blazers 107
gameRecap.excerpt: Jalen Green led the Rockets with 27 points, three rebounds, and five assists as the Rockets defeated the Blazers, 123-107. Alperen Sengun added 19 points, nine rebounds, and six assists as Fred VanVleet totaled 18 points, 10 assists, and four 3PM. Dalano Banton notched a career-high 30 points, along with eight rebounds and five assists as Anfernee Simons (23 points) and Kris Murray (12 points, career-high 11 rebounds, and a career-best seven assists) totaled 35 points. This was Murrays first career double double.
